A: Node.js is a JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 engine that allows running JS code on the server-side.  Q: Why is Node.js popular for backend development?  A: Because it is fast, non-blocking, scalable, and uses JavaScript (same language for frontend + backend).  ---  Day 2: Node.js Modules & npm  Q: What are modules in Node.js? Modules & npm  Q: What are modules in Node.js?  A: Modules are reusable blocks of code. Node.js has built-in modules like fs, http, path, etc.  Q: What is npm?  A: npm (Node Package Manager) is used to install, share, and manage third-party libraries.  ---  Day 3: File System & Asynchronous Nature  Q: How does Node.js handle async tasks?
